  - q: "Car on the other side of the border"
    a: "On most Brazil–Mercosur pairs we can continue with the same car (with the right paperwork). On some routes, switching to a local car right after the crossing is faster and cheaper. Decided upfront."
  - q: "Timing and overnights"
    a: "On long legs one overnight is included at an agreed point (hotel, apartment). It's not 'stop anywhere' — it's part of the plan."
  - q: "Backup scenario"
    a: "For queues, roadworks, weather or rule changes a Plan B is agreed in advance: alternative crossing, extra overnight, time adjustment."
